Incident.Summary: Warrant service - Suspect fled in and from vehicle - CDS and Firearm recovered.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
Scene Processing:

Digital photographs were obtained and attached to this report. All CDS and the firearm was packaged and processed in accordance with MSP policy and procedures. All CDS and the firearm was placed on a property helds (P-343267 / P-343268 / P-343269 / P-343270) and form 67 - chain of custody.

Narrative:

In February of 2023, I, Cpl. Tittle #6005 of the Maryland State Police – Maryland State Apprehension Team / U.S. Marshals – Capital Area Regional Fugitive Task Force, initiated an investigation into a known fugitive, identified as Denard Timothy Wells, B/M, DOB: 2/26/1988. Wells was wanted on a total six (6) warrants for his arrest which are listed as follows:
  1. Assault 1st Degree w/ Handgun and related offenses – Issued on 2/21/2023 – Case# D-07-CR-23-019010 – Anne Arundel County Sheriff’s Office
  2. Flee and Eluding and related offenses – Issued on 12/28/2022 – Case# SE13874 – Maryland State Police Golden Ring Barrack
  3. CDS: Possession with the Intent to Distribute and related offenses – Issued on 11/29/2022 – Case# C-02-CR-22-001354 - Anne Arundel County Sheriff’s Office
  4. Assault 2nd Degree / Burglary 4th Degree and related offenses – Issued on 11/7/2023 – Case# C-02-CR-22-001437 - Anne Arundel County Sheriff’s Office
  5. Assault 2nd Degree and related offenses – Issued on 10/28/2022 – Case# D-07-CR-22-010049 - Anne Arundel County Sheriff’s Office
  6. Escape 2nd Degree and related offenses – Issued on 10/27/2022 – Case# D-07-CR-22-014121 - Anne Arundel County Sheriff’s Office

Upon being assigned the fugitive investigation, Task Force members conducted an in-depth background investigation into Wells’ family, friends, associates, and pattern of life. Wells had a violent criminal history consisting of home invasion and assaults. During the course of the investigation, Task Force members learned Wells was recently involved in a domestic dispute with his girlfriend, Dana Cierra Powell B/F DOB: 6/1/1999. During this incident, Wells is alleged to have brandished a handgun at Powell. Powell called 911 and Wells fled prior to police arriving.

On 3/10/2023, at approximately 1240 hours, I was conducting stationary covert surveillance at 8067 Long Branch Terrace Glen Burnie, MD. This address is associated with Powell and is where the incident occurred. During this time, I observed a subject, later identified as Wells, sitting inside a 2019 gray Chevrolet Malibu, bearing Maryland registration 7EY1065, which was parked on the side of 8067 Long Branch Terrace. After a period of time, Wells exited the vehicle and walked inside the apartment building.

The vehicle was registered to Allcar Leasing Inc. On 3/10/2023, I contacted a law enforcement representative of Allcar Leasing Inc. to inquire about this vehicle. The representative confirmed that the vehicle was currently being rented by Denard Timothy Wells, B/M, DOB: 2/26/1988. The representative advised Wells began renting the vehicle on 2/24/203 and was due to return the vehicle on 3/11/2023.

On 3/13/2023, in the morning hours, I located the 2019 Chevrolet Malibu, bearing Maryland registration 7EY1065, parking in the rear parking lot of the Comfort Inn Hotel, located at 6921 Baltimore Annapolis Blvd Baltimore, MD 21225. I confirmed with the Allcar Leasing representative that Wells was still actively renting the vehicle and was due to return the vehicle now on this date, 3/13/2023.
With this information, additional Task Force members were requested to respond. Task Force members devised an operational plan to conduct stationary covert surveillance on the Chevrolet Malibu in an attempt to identify and arrest Wells. 

While conducting surveillance, Task Force members made contact with management from the Comfort Inn. Task Force members were unable to identify a room associated with Wells.

At approximately 1050 hours, Wells was observed exiting the front door of the hotel and began walking towards the vehicle. Once entering the vehicle, Task Force members converged on the Chevrolet Malibu, while activating their vehicles emergency equipment.

Task Force members began giving Wells loud verbal commands to surrender. Initially, it appeared Wells was going to surrender, however he quickly placed the vehicle in reverse and accelerated rapidly. Wells was initially backed into a parking space. Behind his vehicle was a curb that led down a grass hill to a culvert / ditch.

As Wells accelerated, the vehicle traveled down the hill and into the lower parking lot. Wells was able to place the vehicle in drive and navigate around additional law enforcement vehicles which had their emergency equipment activated.

During the initial point of fleeing, the two front tires of Wells’ vehicle became deflated.

Wells traveled out of the parking lot and made a right turn onto Bell Grove RD towards Hoffman Ave.

Deputy U.S. Marshals assigned to the fugitive Task Force took primary in the pursuit while providing updates via radio.

The vehicle continued on Belle Grove RD towards Ritchie Hwy. Due to the front tires actively deflating, Wells was unable to gain speed.

Wells then made a right turn on 4th Ave at which time the front two wheels were totally deflated, and the vehicle became inoperative. At that time, Wells exited the front driver's seat and fled on foot towards Chatham RD. Task Force members immediately gave chase, never losing sight of Wells. Wells then made a left onto Chatham RD on foot and then made a right into Alley 70. Wells then entered into the rear backyard of 209 5th Ave Brooklyn, MD. Wells ran up onto the rear deck of the residence. As Task Force members and a USMS K9 gained distance, Wells surrendered by putting his hands above his head.

Wells was placed under arrest without further incident.

Wells was escorted to the front of 209 5th Ave at which time Wells complained about being short of breath citing he had asthma. EMS was requested via dispatch from members of the Anne Arundel County Police Department on scene. While awaiting EMS, Wells made several excited utterances that the CDS in the vehicle was his. In addition, Wells stated there was a firearm in the vehicle. 

EMS arrived and evaluated Wells. Wells requested to be transported to the hospital for evaluation. Wells was transported to MedStar Harbor Hospital.

While fleeing on foot, Task Force members observed Wells throw objects from his person in the area of Alley 70. Task Force members quickly located two (2) clear plastic baggies containing suspected crack cocaine. The suspected CDS was photographed in place and then recovered. 

Task Force members conducted a search of the vehicle, which resulted in the following being recovered:
  • One (1) silver Springfield XD9 9mm handgun, serial# S3940695, loaded with 8 rounds of ammunition, including one in the chamber (Located in the center console)
  • One plastic bag, containing a white substance, suspected cocaine, a schedule II controlled dangerous substance. Weight: 107.5 grams (Located on the passenger seat in a black bag)
  • One plastic bag, containing a white substance, suspected cocaine, a schedule II controlled dangerous substance. Weight: 30.8 grams (Located on the passenger seat in a black bag)
  • One bag containing suspected marijuana, a schedule I controlled dangerous substance. Weight: 158.7 grams (Located in a white grocery bag on the rear floorboard behind the driver's seat)
  • Twenty-three small packs containing suspected marijuana, a schedule I controlled dangerous substance. Weight: 144 grams (Located in a white grocery bag on the rear floorboard behind the driver's seat)
  • Ten (10) pills of suspected oxycodone, a schedule II controlled dangerous substance. (Located in a prescription bottle on the floorboard - prescription label was obliterated) 
The following was recovered from where Task Force members observed Wells throw something in the area of Alley 70:
  • One plastic bag, containing a white rock like substance, suspected crack cocaine, a schedule II controlled dangerous substance. Weight: 90.3 grams
  • One plastic bag, containing a white rock like substance, suspected crack cocaine, a schedule II controlled dangerous substance. Weight: 30.5 grams
Wells was later evaluated and released from MedStar Harbor Hospital. Wells was transported to the Maryland State Police Glen Burnie Barrack. Upon arriving, a secondary search was conducted of Wells’ person. Located on Wells’ person was the following:
  • One glass jar, containing a yellowish liquid substance, suspected Phencyclidine, a schedule II controlled dangerous substance. Weight: 50.8 grams (Located in a front zipper pocket in Wells' pants)
  • Two small baggies, containing a white rock like substance, suspected crack cocaine, a schedule II controlled dangerous substance. Weight: 2.4 grams (Wells' front left pants change pocket)

I know through my training, knowledge, and experience as a Maryland State Trooper that the above listed to be a controlled dangerous substance. The above listed CDS was packaged in a sufficient manner to indicate the distribution of the same. 

The vehicle was towed by White Huff Towing. Contact was made with Allcar Leasing and provided with the tow company information and the MSP case number associated with this incident. 

The Maryland State Police Gun Center was contacted regarding Wells and the firearm recovered. The Gun Center conducted a work-up which revealed Wells was prohibited from possession firearms and / or ammunition for the following reasons.
Prohibiting Offenses:
  • Convicted on 8/2/2007 in the Circuit Court for Anne Arundel County, Maryland for Wear, Carry, and Transport a Handgun Case# 02K07000837
  • Convicted on 12/12/2007 in the Circuit Court for Anne Arundel County, Maryland for CDS: Possession with the Intent to Distribute Narcotic Case# 02K07002151
  • Convicted on 10/24/2023 in the Circuit Court for Anne Arundel County, Maryland for CDS Manufacture / Distribute Narcotic Case# 02K09001924
Wells was transported to the Anne Arundel County Detention Center where he was served with the six (6) open warrants and charged on-view for charges related to this incident. 

All events occurred in Anne Arundel County, Maryland.

On 3/15/2023, a subpoena was issued through Baltimore County, Maryland for the rental agreement in reference to this investigation. The subpoena was served on Allcar Leasing Inc. and the rental agreement was obtained. 

The subpoena and rental agreement has been attached to this report. 

Case remains closed by arrest.

On 5/4/2023, D/Sgt. Logsdon # 2064, of the Maryland State Police - Glen Burnie Barrack, conducted a test fire of the firearm, Springfield XD 9mm handgun serial# S3940695, seized during this investigation. The firearm was found to be operable. The test fire certificate has been attached to this report. 

Case remains closed by arrest.
